# Periodic Review & Adjustment of Cybersecurity Risk Management Strategy – Audit Checklist

## 1. Defined Review & Adjustment Process
- [ ] Does the organization have a defined process for periodically reviewing and adjusting its cybersecurity risk management strategy?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Dokumentierter Review-Zyklus für die Strategie
- Genehmigung durch Management / CISO
- Integration in Governance- und ISMS-Prozesse
- Historie von Review-Meetings

---

## 2. Incorporating Organizational Changes
- [ ] How does the organization identify and incorporate changes in organizational requirements, risks, and threats into the review and adjustment of the strategy?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Dokumentierte Change-Management-Prozesse
- Threat Intelligence und Risikoanalysen berücksichtigt
- Nachweis der Anpassung der Strategie nach Änderungen
- Protokolle von Review-Meetings

---

## 3. Stakeholder Input
- [ ] Are there mechanisms to gather input from key stakeholders (business units, IT, security team, leadership) on the effectiveness and relevance of the strategy?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Workshops, Meetings oder Surveys dokumentiert
- Stakeholder-Feedback protokolliert
- Integration des Feedbacks in die Strategie-Reviews
- Nachweis der Berücksichtigung des Inputs in Entscheidungen

---

## 4. Assessment Criteria & Metrics
- [ ] What criteria or metrics does the organization use to assess the adequacy and coverage of the strategy in addressing its requirements and risks?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- KPI/KRI für Strategie-Wirksamkeit
- Bewertungsmatrix für Coverage und Adequacy
- Reports aus Risk Management Tools
- Benchmarking gegen Standards oder Best Practices

---

## 5. Analysis & Identification of Improvements
- [ ] How does the organization analyze the results of the strategy review to identify areas for improvement or adjustment?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Gap-Analysen oder Lessons Learned
- Dokumentierte Vorschläge für Anpassungen
- Priorisierung von Maßnahmen
- Management-Reports oder Steering Committee Minutes

---

## 6. Alignment with Overall Risk Management
- [ ] Are the adjustments to the strategy aligned with the organization's overall risk management approach and business objectives?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Nachweis der Konsistenz zwischen Cybersecurity-Strategie und Enterprise Risk Management
- Dokumentierte Abstimmung mit Business-Strategie
- Genehmigung von Anpassungen durch Management
- Integration in Governance-Framework

---

## 7. Communication & Implementation
- [ ] What processes are in place to ensure that the updated strategy is effectively communicated and implemented across the organization?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Kommunikationsplan dokumentiert
- Awareness- und Trainingsprogramme
- Nachweis der Implementierung in Teams und Abteilungen
- Feedback-Mechanismen zur Wirksamkeit

---

## 8. Training & Guidance
- [ ] Does the organization provide training or guidance to support the implementation of the adjusted strategy?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Trainingsprogramme oder E-Learning-Nachweise
- Leitfäden oder SOPs für Mitarbeitende
- KPI/KRI Monitoring der Teilnahme
- Integration in fortlaufende Schulungspläne

---

## 9. Leadership Commitment
- [ ] How does leadership demonstrate their commitment to the regular review and adjustment of the strategy?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Teilnahme an Review-Meetings durch Führung
- Ressourcenbereitstellung für Anpassungen
- Offizielle Kommunikation des Führungscommitments
- Nachweis der Einbindung in strategische Entscheidungen

---

## 10. Monitoring Effectiveness
- [ ] Are there mechanisms in place to monitor the effectiveness of the adjusted cybersecurity risk management strategy?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- KPI/KRI Tracking für implementierte Anpassungen
- Follow-up Audits oder Reviews
- Reports an Management / Board
- Lessons Learned aus Monitoring und Vorfällen
